This was the first time in three career meetings that Doncic had beat guard Dragic, as Dallas snapped a six-game losing skid to MiamiIn what appears to be a growing trend in the NBA, Miami was undone by poor shooting from the three-point rangeElsewhere, De'Andre Hunter scored 23 points, and Trae Young chipped in 21 as the Atlanta Hawks bounced back from giving up 145 points in their last game to beat the cold-shooting Brooklyn Nets 114-96 in New York